  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section id="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro">
        <span class="label">Frequently asked questions</span>
        <h2>The objections you <span class="accent">will have.</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-1">
            "My client is a CTO or IT manager — they don't respond to cold email."
            <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-1" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">CTOs and IT managers respond to cold email when the message is technically credible and specific to their context. What doesn't work is a generic marketing agency approach. The difference is who writes the sequence.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-2">
            "Cold email will burn my technical reputation."
            <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-2" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Poorly executed cold email burns. Well-segmented cold email — with a qualified list, dedicated warmed domain, and technical tone — does not. The operation is designed to preserve your reputation, not compromise it.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-3">
            "My sales cycle is 60–90 days. Is outbound worth it?"
            <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-3" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">A long cycle is exactly why outbound is necessary. The longer the cycle, the earlier you need to enter the conversation. Outbound puts you in front of the decision-maker before they know they need you.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-4">
            "I don't have time to implement one more thing right now."
            <div class="faq-icon">+</div>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-4" role="region">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">You don't implement anything. Ötzi implements it. You participate in a 30-minute diagnostic call and a monthly 45-minute meeting. Everything else is operated by us.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


